    <string id="str_culture_description.empire_w" text="The Bengalis hold the rich, water-laced delta of the east, the wealthiest subah of the empire. Grown fat on rice, muslin and the river trade, the Nawabs of Bengal rule in the empire's name but increasingly for themselves. Their soldiers are at home in flooded paddy and on river boats, and their treasuries are the envy of every prince in Hindostan." />
